Yen Drops Against Most Counterparts as Gains in Shares Curb Refuge Demand

-- B y   M a s a k i   K o n d o
-- 
2011-09-01T00:42:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-01/yen-drops-against-most-counterparts-as-gains-in-shares-curb-refuge-demand.html
The yen fell against most of its
major counterparts as gains in Asian stocks reduced demand for
 Japan ’s currency as a refuge.  The yen declined to as weak as 110.48 per  euro  before
trading at 110.28 at 9:41 a.m. in  Tokyo  from 110.16 in  New York 
yesterday. Japan’s currency was at 76.76 against the dollar from
76.66.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Masaki Kondo in Singapore at 
